    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.1",
      "en": "AtomOS is Elemento's native Linux-based virtualization platform for sovereign private cloud, edge, AI infrastructure and VMware replacement scenarios. VMware, Proxmox and other hypervisors are third-party endpoints in the same Atomosquare fabric.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.10",
      "en": "Mainline kernel and RHEL-compliant userspace mean you get security fixes and updates as soon as they're available — no waiting for vendor backports or custom patches.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.11",
      "en": "Leverage the full breadth of Linux hardware support. New devices, GPUs, and NICs work out of the box with upstream drivers.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.12",
      "en": "Automatic passthrough",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.13",
      "en": "VM CPU performance",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.14",
      "en": "VMs per Host",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.15",
      "en": "Faster Deployments",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.16",
      "en": "Get AtomOS running on your infrastructure quickly and easily",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.17",
      "en": "Enterprise-grade features designed for production workloads",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.18",
      "en": "Supported via qcow2 format for efficient storage utilization and dynamic disk allocation.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.19",
      "en": "Over fast LAN + shared FS for zero-downtime workload mobility.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.2",
      "en": "Built on proven KVM and QEMU technology with RHEL compatibility and no vendor lock-in",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.20",
      "en": "Full support for secure boot and Virtual Trusted Platform Module for enhanced security.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.21",
      "en": "Native Electros CLI for automation and scripting, plus standard Linux virtualization tools.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.22",
      "en": "Automatically distributes workloads across nodes without needing a central controller. Each server makes local decisions to balance traffic, ensuring high performance, resilience, and seamless scalability.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.23",
      "en": "Any shared FS: GlusterFS, Ceph, NFS, iSCSI, etc. - flexible storage options for your infrastructure.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.24",
      "en": "How AtomOS compares to the industry-leading virtualization platform",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.25",
      "en": "Calculate how much you could save with AtomOS compared to VMware. Discover how our virtualization solution helps you escape rising costs, without compromising enterprise-level reliability.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.26",
      "en": "Standalone calculator page →",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.27",
      "en": "AtomOS supports a wide range of Linux and Windows guest OSes for flexible deployment scenarios",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.28",
      "en": "For performance, use raw or qcow2 on stable Linux-native FS (EXT4, XFS). Avoid BTRFS/ReFS stacking with qcow2.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.29",
      "en": "Autonomous clustering without centralized management",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.3",
      "en": "Secure boot, ECC memory support, and advanced GPU passthrough for production workloads",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.30",
      "en": "AtomOS implements Elemento's C4 protocol for automatic peer discovery and trust-based node linking. No need for orchestrators, matchmaker services, or controller VMs.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.31",
      "en": "Every host participates in its own discovery and control fabric without external dependencies.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.32",
      "en": "From free community use to enterprise production deployments",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.33",
      "en": "Per server, regardless of CPU cores or VM count",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.34",
      "en": "Per server, regardless of CPU cores or VM count",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.35",
      "en": "Our pricing model incentivizes efficient resource utilization and sustainable infrastructure choices",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.36",
      "en": "Unlike CPU-core or VM-count based licensing, AtomOS's server-based pricing encourages organizations to maximize the value of each physical server. This drives investment in larger, more efficient hardware that can host more workloads with better performance per watt.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.37",
      "en": "By charging per server rather than per CPU core or VM, we encourage organizations to choose powerful, efficient hardware that can handle more workloads with less energy consumption.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.38",
      "en": "Common questions about AtomOS deployment and usage",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.39",
      "en": "Runs on x86_64 servers (Intel/AMD) with virtualization support. Also runs as nested guest in AWS/GCP/Azure metal VMs.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.4",
      "en": "Seamless integration with public clouds and hybrid infrastructure management",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.40",
      "en": "Yes. GPU passthrough is supported for NVIDIA (GTX960+) and AMD cards, tested for gaming, 3D rendering, and inference engines.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.41",
      "en": "No. Unlike vSphere or Proxmox, clustering is embedded — every host participates in its own discovery and control fabric.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.42",
      "en": "Core hypervisor is open. Electros and C4 protocol orchestration layers are licensed with commercial support options.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.43",
      "en": "AtomOS works seamlessly with other Elemento products to create a complete cloud platform",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.44",
      "en": "Orchestration dashboard and CLI for managing VMs across public clouds and on-prem infrastructure from a single interface.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.45",
      "en": "Unified API that maps every cloud provider into a single programmable interface for seamless orchestration.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.46",
      "en": "Pre-configured hardware servers with AtomOS included and perpetual licensing for development and production workloads.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.47",
      "en": "Experience the power of Linux-native virtualization for your infrastructure",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.5",
      "en": "No need to be fancy to be just right. At Elemento, we believe in the Linux paradigm. We didn't want to reinvent virtualization from scratch, forgetting all the great work behind KVM and QEMU over the past 30 years.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.6",
      "en": "Instead, we built on top of KVM and QEMU to create AtomOS , a hypervisor that is open , portable , and secure .",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.7",
      "en": "No customisation. No forks. Just a rock-solid, upstream-aligned base that powers enterprise-grade reliability.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.8",
      "en": "AtomOS runs on top of a RHEL-compliant underlying OS — without customisation or forks. This means you get the full benefit of Red Hat's ecosystem: battle-tested stability, enterprise-grade support, and complete compatibility with the RHEL ecosystem.",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.atomos.p.9",
      "en": "The kernel is mainline Linux — no vendor patches or proprietary extensions. This empowers incredible hardware support and super fast security updates (and updates in general).",
      "it": "",
      "fr": "",
      "source": "atomos.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
